[
    {
        "content": "<p>Is anyone using NixOS as their dev environment for building kernels with Rust enabled? I'm currently stuck at <a href=\"https://docs.kernel.org/rust/quick-start.html#rust-standard-library-source\">this</a> step, adding the Rust standard library source. Here's what I have until now in my nix file:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">let</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"p\">#</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Pinned</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">nixpkgs</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">deterministic</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Last</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">updated</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"mi\">12</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"mf\">21.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">pkgs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">fetchTarball</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/archive/0aeab749216e4c073cece5d34bc01b79e717c3e0.tar.gz\"</span><span class=\"p\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{};</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pkgs</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mkShell</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">buildInputs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pkgs</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cargo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pkgs</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rustc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pkgs</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">bindgen</span><span class=\"p\">];</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">hardeningDisable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pkgs</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">hardeningDisable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">++</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s\">\"strictoverflow\"</span><span class=\"p\">];</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>If I use rustup everything works, but now I'm trying to avoid it. The thing is I cannot extract the sources into the toolchain’s installation folder, because it is read-only in NixOS.</p>",
        "id": 448935895,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1720036025
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would strongly suggest using flakes :)</p>\n<p>because then you can use <a href=\"https://github.com/nix-community/fenix\">fenix</a> and avoid rustup that way</p>",
        "id": 448937378,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1720036655
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'll look into it, thanks</p>",
        "id": 448938109,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1720036899
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For the Rust standard library, see <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20240701183625.665574-14-ojeda@kernel.org/\">https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20240701183625.665574-14-ojeda@kernel.org/</a></p>\n<p>i.e. <code>RUST_LIB_SRC = \"${pkgs.rust.packages.stable.rustPlatform.rustLibSrc}\";</code></p>",
        "id": 448940594,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1720037648
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But I would listen to Benno and use fenix instead -- I do not actually use Nix, I only tested that setting the variable worked (for a Nix shell) :)</p>",
        "id": 448940786,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1720037713
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I use this flake.nix:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Nix\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"ss\">description</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"A nix flake for compiling the kernel with rust\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"ss\">inputs</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    nixpkgs_old<span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"ss\">url</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span>\n      <span class=\"s2\">\"github:NixOS/nixpkgs/2d5c19598ad493b31d522ba89d2e683c5964b69a\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n    nixpkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"ss\">url</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"github:NixOS/nixpkgs/nixos-unstable\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n    rust-overlay<span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"ss\">url</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"github:oxalica/rust-overlay\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n  <span class=\"ss\">outputs</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span> self<span class=\"p\">,</span> nixpkgs<span class=\"p\">,</span> nixpkgs_old<span class=\"p\">,</span> rust-overlay <span class=\"p\">}:</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">let</span>\n      <span class=\"ss\">overlays</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">import</span> rust-overlay<span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"p\">];</span>\n      <span class=\"ss\">system</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"x86_64-linux\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"ss\">pkgs</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"nb\">import</span> nixpkgs <span class=\"p\">{</span> <span class=\"k\">inherit</span> system overlays<span class=\"p\">;</span> <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n      <span class=\"ss\">pkgs_old</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"nb\">import</span> nixpkgs_old <span class=\"p\">{</span> <span class=\"k\">inherit</span> system overlays<span class=\"p\">;</span> <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n      <span class=\"ss\">rust</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>rust-bin<span class=\"o\">.</span>stable<span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"s2\">\"1.78.0\"</span><span class=\"o\">.</span>default<span class=\"o\">.</span>override <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"ss\">extensions</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"rust-src\"</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"rust-analyzer\"</span> <span class=\"p\">];</span>\n      <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n      <span class=\"ss\">rust_platform</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>makeRustPlatform <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"ss\">cargo</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> rust<span class=\"p\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"ss\">rustc</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> rust<span class=\"p\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n      devShells<span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"si\">${</span>system<span class=\"si\">}</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"ss\">default</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span>\n        pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>mkShell<span class=\"o\">.</span>override <span class=\"p\">{</span> <span class=\"ss\">stdenv</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>clangStdenv<span class=\"p\">;</span> <span class=\"p\">}</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n          <span class=\"ss\">buildInputs</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span>\n            rust\n            <span class=\"p\">(</span>pkgs_old<span class=\"o\">.</span>rust-bindgen<span class=\"o\">.</span>override <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n              <span class=\"ss\">rust-bindgen-unwrapped</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span>\n                pkgs_old<span class=\"o\">.</span>rust-bindgen-unwrapped<span class=\"o\">.</span>override <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n                  <span class=\"ss\">rustPlatform</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> rust_platform<span class=\"p\">;</span>\n                  <span class=\"ss\">clang</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>clang<span class=\"p\">;</span>\n                <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n            <span class=\"p\">})</span>\n            pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>util-linux\n            <span class=\"p\">(</span>pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>llvmPackages<span class=\"o\">.</span>bintools<span class=\"o\">.</span>override <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n              <span class=\"ss\">sharedLibraryLoader</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"no\">null</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n            <span class=\"p\">})</span>\n            pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>elfutils\n            pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>flex\n            pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>bison\n            pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>bc\n            pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>perl\n            pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>openssl\n            pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>ncurses\n            pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>bear\n          <span class=\"p\">];</span>\n        <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n    <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Depending on the kernel sources you may have to edit the rust version.<br>\nThe specific nixpkgs commit is for bindgen 0.65.1.<br>\nSome packges may be missing or not needed depending on your uses</p>\n<p>you would use this with <code>nix develop</code></p>",
        "id": 448962981,
        "sender_full_name": "Marcel Wiesenhöfer",
        "timestamp": 1720046526
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am using NixOS to boot system closures on bare metal for benchmarking purposes. I use <a href=\"https://github.com/DeterminateSystems/nix-netboot-serve\"><code>nix-netboot-serve</code></a> for that with a custom kernel derivation.</p>",
        "id": 449020753,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1720078288
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I combine that with <a href=\"https://laminar.ohwg.net/\">Laminar CI</a> and a bit of scripting to control the power state of the target nodes.</p>",
        "id": 449020942,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1720078356
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I do something like this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Nix\"><pre><span></span><code>    <span class=\"ss\">rustc-version</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>lib<span class=\"o\">.</span>strings<span class=\"o\">.</span>removeSuffix <span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">builtins</span><span class=\"o\">.</span>readFile <span class=\"p\">(</span>\n      pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>runCommand <span class=\"s2\">\"rustc-version\"</span> <span class=\"p\">{}</span> <span class=\"s2\">\" cd </span><span class=\"si\">${</span>cfg<span class=\"o\">.</span>src<span class=\"si\">}</span><span class=\"s2\">; scripts/min-tool-version.sh rustc &gt; $out\"</span><span class=\"p\">));</span>\n    <span class=\"ss\">kernelRust</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> rust-pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>rust-bin<span class=\"o\">.</span>stable<span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"si\">${</span>rustc-version<span class=\"si\">}</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"o\">.</span>complete<span class=\"p\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"ss\">llvm-version</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>lib<span class=\"o\">.</span>strings<span class=\"o\">.</span>removeSuffix <span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">builtins</span><span class=\"o\">.</span>readFile <span class=\"p\">(</span>\n      pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>runCommand <span class=\"s2\">\"llvm-version\"</span> <span class=\"p\">{}</span> <span class=\"s s-Multiline\">''</span>\n<span class=\"s s-Multiline\">        </span><span class=\"si\">${</span>kernelRust<span class=\"si\">}</span><span class=\"s s-Multiline\">/bin/rustc --version --verbose | grep 'LLVM version' | sed -r 's/.* ([0-9]+)\\.[0-9]+\\.[0-9]/\\1/' &gt; $out</span>\n<span class=\"s s-Multiline\">      ''</span><span class=\"p\">));</span>\n    <span class=\"ss\">kernelLlvm</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>buildPackages<span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"s2\">\"llvmPackages_</span><span class=\"si\">${</span>llvm-version<span class=\"si\">}</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n    <span class=\"ss\">rawKernel</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>callPackage <span class=\"l\">./kernel.nix</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"k\">inherit</span>\n        pkgs\n        lib\n        kernelLlvm\n        kernelRust\n        kernelBindgen<span class=\"p\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"ss\">stdenv</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>stdenv<span class=\"p\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"ss\">kernelSrc</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> cfg<span class=\"o\">.</span>src<span class=\"p\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"ss\">configFragments</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> cfg<span class=\"o\">.</span>fragments<span class=\"p\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n    <span class=\"ss\">kernel</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> lib<span class=\"o\">.</span>recurseIntoAttrs <span class=\"p\">(</span>pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>linuxKernel<span class=\"o\">.</span>packagesFor rawKernel<span class=\"p\">);</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Then you can use it like a regular kernel and build a regular NixOS system closure with it.</p>",
        "id": 449022083,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1720078754
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"546447\">@Benno Lossin</span> <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"412307\">@Finn Behrens</span> I am trying to set up a nix dev shell for cross compiling from x86_64 to aarch64, but I think I am doing something wrong:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Nix\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"ss\">description</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"Kernel dev flake\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"ss\">inputs</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    nixpkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"ss\">url</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"github:nixos/nixpkgs?ref=nixos-24.05\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"ss\">rust-overlay</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"ss\">url</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"github:oxalica/rust-overlay\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n      inputs<span class=\"o\">.</span>nixpkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"ss\">follows</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"nixpkgs\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n  <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n  <span class=\"ss\">outputs</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span> self<span class=\"p\">,</span> nixpkgs<span class=\"p\">,</span> rust-overlay <span class=\"p\">}:</span> <span class=\"k\">let</span>\n    <span class=\"ss\">overlays</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">import</span> rust-overlay<span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"p\">];</span>\n    <span class=\"ss\">pkgs</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"nb\">import</span> nixpkgs <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"k\">inherit</span> overlays<span class=\"p\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"ss\">system</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"x86_64-linux\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n    <span class=\"ss\">pkgsArm</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"nb\">import</span> nixpkgs <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"ss\">system</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"x86_64-linux\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"ss\">crossSystem</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"ss\">config</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n    <span class=\"ss\">rustArm</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> rust-overlay<span class=\"o\">.</span>lib<span class=\"o\">.</span>mkRustBin <span class=\"p\">{}</span> pkgsArm<span class=\"o\">.</span>buildPackages<span class=\"p\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"k\">in</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n      devShells<span class=\"o\">.</span>x86_64-linux<span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"ss\">default</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>mkShell <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"ss\">packages</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"k\">with</span> pkgs<span class=\"p\">;</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span>\n          llvm_18\n          clang_18\n          llvmPackages_18<span class=\"o\">.</span>bintools\n          llvmPackages_18<span class=\"o\">.</span>bintools-unwrapped\n          rust-bin<span class=\"o\">.</span>stable<span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"s2\">\"1.78.0\"</span><span class=\"o\">.</span>complete\n          bison\n          flex\n          pahole\n          bc\n          elfutils\n          openssl\n          perl\n          kmod\n          rsync\n          just\n        <span class=\"p\">];</span>\n        <span class=\"ss\">HOST_CFLAGS</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"-I</span><span class=\"si\">${</span>pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>elfutils<span class=\"si\">}</span><span class=\"s2\">/include\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n      devShells<span class=\"o\">.</span>x86_64-linux<span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"ss\">amd64</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> pkgsArm<span class=\"o\">.</span>callPackage <span class=\"p\">(</span>\n        <span class=\"p\">{</span>mkShell<span class=\"p\">,</span> llvm_18<span class=\"p\">,</span> clang_18<span class=\"p\">}:</span> mkShell <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"ss\">nativeBuildInputs</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span>  <span class=\"p\">[</span>\n          llvm_18\n          clang_18\n          <span class=\"c1\"># llvmPackages_18.bintools</span>\n          <span class=\"c1\"># llvmPackages_18.bintools-unwrapped</span>\n          <span class=\"c1\"># rustArm.stable.\"1.78.0\".complete</span>\n          <span class=\"c1\"># bison</span>\n          <span class=\"c1\"># flex</span>\n          <span class=\"c1\"># pahole</span>\n          <span class=\"c1\"># bc</span>\n          <span class=\"c1\"># elfutils</span>\n          <span class=\"c1\"># openssl</span>\n          <span class=\"c1\"># perl</span>\n          <span class=\"c1\"># kmod</span>\n          <span class=\"c1\"># rsync</span>\n          <span class=\"c1\"># just</span>\n        <span class=\"p\">];</span>\n        <span class=\"ss\">HOST_CFLAGS</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"-I</span><span class=\"si\">${</span>pkgs<span class=\"o\">.</span>elfutils<span class=\"si\">}</span><span class=\"s2\">/include\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"ss\">ARCH</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"aarch64\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"ss\">CROSS_COMPILE</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"aarch64-\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"p\">})</span> <span class=\"p\">{}</span> <span class=\"p\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>When I run this, nix starts compiling <code>llvm</code>and <code>clang</code>. Should I not be able to get those cached?</p>",
        "id": 457340604,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1723115826
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>IIRC cross is way less good cached, so could be that actually not cached</p>",
        "id": 457340839,
        "sender_full_name": "Fiona Behrens",
        "timestamp": 1723115911
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>sadly nix does not have a good concept of cross compiling able tools</p>",
        "id": 457340871,
        "sender_full_name": "Fiona Behrens",
        "timestamp": 1723115926
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>you could try to use host clang, but be aware of the -target overriding (see <a href=\"https://kloenk.eu/posts/build-linux-on-m1-macos/\">https://kloenk.eu/posts/build-linux-on-m1-macos/</a>)</p>",
        "id": 457340950,
        "sender_full_name": "Fiona Behrens",
        "timestamp": 1723115957
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I ended up using all the LLVM bits from outside of the devShell, since it already supports a large set of targets, including arm64. Then it worked fine, once I removed the (wrong) CROSS_COMPILE variable and changed ARCH to <code>arm64</code>.</p>",
        "id": 459380682,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1723184354
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"498029\">Andreas Hindborg</span> has marked this topic as resolved.</p>",
        "id": 459380690,
        "sender_full_name": "Notification Bot",
        "timestamp": 1723184360
    }
]